This processing constitutes:
Handling activity data
This type of service allows the Owner to use the activity data collected by your device in order for Forest (iOS version) to operate or to provide specific features. This may include movements, heartbeat, change in altitude or data about the surroundings.
Depending on what is described below, third parties may be involved in the activity tracking.
Most devices allow for the User to control which Data is accessed or stored.
Apple Healthkit
If you turn on the Healthkit-related feature in Forest, Forest will request access to the Healthkit store in your device. The function is only limited to storing the mindfulness data which is generated in the app by you to Healthkit. We do not collect or use any of your health data from Healthkit store, and we will not reveal your mindfulness data to third-party companies.
This processing constitutes:
a Sale in California
a Sharing in California
Hosting and backend infrastructure
This type of service has the purpose of hosting Data and files that enable Forest (iOS version) to run and be distributed as well as to provide a ready-made infrastructure to run specific features or parts of Forest (iOS version).
Some of these services work through geographically distributed servers, making it difficult to determine the actual location where the Personal Data are stored.
