Further information about the processing of Personal Data
Browser Extension API
Forest (Browser Extension version) requires the permission to "Read and change all your data on the websites you visit." of your browser. This permission is needed for the following purposes:
- Check the URL of the website the User is visiting against the blacklist or whitelist. The check is done locally. The URL of the website the User is visiting, the blacklist and the whitelist are not collected.
- Display the overlay if the User visits a URL in a blacklist or not in the whitelist.
